    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, so you're saying religious freedom is basically secondary to the state? if a group's core identity is tied to their faith, doesn't forcing them to follow laws that violate that identity basically strip them of their actual freedom? it feels like you're saying secularism is more important than the actual rights of the people living in the society.",
