      "content": "The concept of religious freedom is not an absolute license to defy the law; it is a right *within* the boundaries of a functioning civil society. True freedom requires that all individuals abide by the same rules, which is the essence of secular governance. When a religious practice directly infringes upon the rights or safety of others, the state's obligation to protect those rights overrides the claim of religious exemption.",
